
[1]hagard

   HAG'ARD, a.

   1. Literally, having a ragged look, as if hacked or gashed. Hence,
   lean; meager; rough; having eyes sunk in their orbits; ugly.

   2. Wild; fierce; intractable; as a hagard hawk.

                                 HAG'ARD, n.

   1. Any thing wild and intractable.

   2. A species of hawk.

   3. A hag.
